'''Scott E. Yancey ''' (born July 9, 1969)<ref name= CABI>{{cite web|url= http://www.californiabirthindex.org/birth/scott_e_yancey_born_1969_10805087|title= Scott E. Yancey, born 07/09/1969|publisher= California Birth Index|accessdate= March 2, 2016}}</ref> is a TV personality, businessman, real estate investor, and author.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.amazon.com/Scott-Yancey/e/B00GHSK5TK|title=Amazon.com: Scott Yancey: Books, Biography, Blog, Audiobooks, Kindle|website=www.amazon.com|access-date=2016-07-13}}</ref> He is best known for his role on the [[A&E (TV channel)|A&E]] television series, ''[[Flipping Vegas]]'', a modern reality TV show in which Scott and his wife, Amie Yancey<ref>{{cite news|last=Katsilometes|first=John|title=Real lives of reality TV stars|url=http://www.lasvegassun.com/news/2014/apr/27/real-lives-reality-tv-stars/|accessdate=3 May 2014|newspaper=Las Vegas Sun|date=April 27, 2014}}</ref> purchase and repair dilapidated homes in the [[Las Vegas Valley]], and attempt to flip them for profit.<ref>{{cite web|title=News 3 Las Vegas|url=http://www.mynews3.com/mediacenter/local.aspx?videoID=4982112|accessdate=25 April 2014}}</ref>

==Early life==
Yancey was born on July 9, 1969 in [[Los Angeles County, California]],<ref name= CABI/> and raised in [[Studio City, Los Angeles|Studio City, California]],<ref>{{cite web|url= http://www.huffingtonpost.com/scott-yancey/|title= Scott Yancey biography|work= The Huffington Post|accessdate= March 2, 2016}}</ref> where he attended [[North Hollywood High School]].{{citation needed|date=July 2016}}

==Personal life==
Yancey married his future ''[[Flipping Vegas]]'' costar, Amie, on January 26, 2000.<ref name=IMDb>{{cite news|title=IMDb Biography|url=https://www.imdb.com/name/nm4043513/bio?ref_=nm_ov_bth_nm|accessdate=25 April 2014}}</ref>{{better source|date=July 2016}} Yancey has [[attention deficit hyperactivity disorder]].<ref name= VS>{{cite web|url= http://vegasseven.com/2014/05/28/seven-questions-scott-yancey/|title= Seven Questions for Scott Yancey|date= May 28, 2014|website= Vegas Seven|accessdate= May 6, 2016|last= Acuña|first= Jessi|quote='''I'm not a college graduate. I went to probably five colleges, and I dropped out of them all. I have ADD.'''}}</ref> As of 2014, the couple had a pet dog, a [[dachshund]] named Tallulah.<ref>{{cite web|title=A&E TV's Cast of Flipping Vegas|url=http://www.aetv.com/flipping-vegas/cast/amie-yancey|publisher=A&E TV|accessdate=25 April 2014}}</ref> The couple also owns two [[Rhodesian_Ridgeback|Rhodesian ridgeback]] dogs named Flip and Zuma, two [[Friesian_horse|friesian horses]] named Henke and Tieme, two mini pigs named Bacon Bits and Lucy, and a mini donkey named JackAss.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.instagram.com/scott_yancey/|title=Scott Yancey (@scott_yancey) • Instagram photos and videos|website=www.instagram.com|access-date=2016-07-13}}</ref>

==Career==

=== Real estate ===
Yancey made his first real estate deal at the age of 14,<ref name=IMDb/> when he received an insurance settlement of $30,000, which he used to purchase the 2nd deed of trust for a home mortgage as an investment with a 14% interest rate.{{citation needed|date=July 2016}}

While enrolled in college, Yancey was hired to be a runner by Walter J. Plumb III, a Real Estate Attorney and investor. Yancey continued to work with Plumb assisting in multiple real estate<ref>{{cite web|title=Biography|url=http://www.scottyancey.com/meet-real-estate-guru-scott-yancey/|accessdate=25 April 2014}}</ref> transactions such as the purchase of a 40-unit apartment complex and converting it to condos along with assembling dozens of land deals subdividing them into over 3000 lots. Now working independently of Plumb, Yancey began developing retail department stores in [[Las Vegas]], [[Provo, Utah]], and [[Tempe, Arizona]].{{citation needed|date=July 2016}}

After selling his department stores and choosing to return to his real estate roots, Yancey relocated to Las Vegas in 1994.{{citation needed|date=July 2016}} In 2008, Yancey founded the Las Vegas-based '''Goliath Company''',<ref>{{cite web |url= http://jessicafryman.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/08/JDF_LVRJ_072611.pdf|title= Local couple turn Vegas' for-sale homes into multimillion-dollar residences|last= Fryman|first= Jessica|date= 26 July 2011|work= [[Las Vegas Review-Journal]]|access-date= 22 October 2015|page= 1|quote='''Scott founded the real estate company Goliath Company in 2008.'''}}</ref> a [[real estate broker]]age and [[investment firm]]. Goliath Company focuses on investment properties, the buy & hold approach and finding land to entitle and subsidize by selling to large private companies; which they have managed to do for a few thousand lots.{{citation needed|date=July 2016}}

=== ''Flipping Vegas'' ===
{{main article|Flipping Vegas}}
In 2010, Yancey and Lovable Scoundrels Productions created the television series ''Flipping Vegas''.<ref>{{Citation|title=Flipping Vegas|date=2011-06-18|url=https://www.imdb.com/title/tt1714050/|accessdate=2016-07-13}}</ref> [[A&E (TV channel)|A&E]] originally premiered the series on June 18, 2011. In addition to starring in the show,<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://lasvegassun.com/vegasdeluxe/2013/dec/05/flipping-vegas-yancey-reality-tv-real-estate-new-s/|title=Photos: Flipping out on the set of A&E's 'Flipping Vegas' with Scott and Amie Yancey|last=Domanick|first=Andrea|work=Las Vegas Sun|date=2013-12-05|access-date=2016-07-13}}</ref> Yancey also served as an executive producer. The show concluded its fifth season on September 27, 2014.

=== Yancey Events ===
The Yanceys created Yancey Events as a way to help others learn about investing in real estate.<ref name=Highya>{{Cite web|url=http://www.highya.com/scott-yancey-reviews|title=Scott Yancey Reviews - Is it a Scam or Legit?|website=HighYa|access-date=2016-07-13}}</ref> <ref name=Popsugar>{{cite web|last1=Winterfeldt|first1=Maggie|title=The Stars of Flipping Vegas Are Accused of Leading a Shameful Real Estate Scam|url=http://www.popsugar.com/home/Flipping-Vegas-Star-Scott-Yancey-Accused-Real-Estate-Scam-41012464|website=POPSUGAR Home|accessdate=29 November 2016}}</ref> Using their stardom from ''Flipping Vegas'', coupled with the knowledge and experience they have gained from years in the business, salespeople working for the company travel across the United States and sell educational [[seminar]]s on how to properly invest in real estate.<ref name=Highya/> Many participants of the events have criticized them as being a scam.<ref name=Popsugar/>
<ref>{{cite web|url=http://vegasseven.com/2017/02/16/clicked-stories-last-seven-years/|title=The Most Clicked-on Stories of the Last Seven Years|website=VegasSeven|accessdate=22 June 2018}}</ref>
<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbb.org/stlouis/news-events/bbb-warnings/2016/06/bbb-warning-on-visionary-events/|title=BBB: Consumers Should Approach Visionary Events Real Estate Investment Seminars With Caution|website=BBB|accessdate=22 June 2018}} '''"Yancey Events, operated by 'Flipping Vegas' TV personality Scott Yancey, has an 'F' rating with Utah BBB, the lowest possible, with more than 40 complaints.  Most of those complaints allege deceptive and misleading marketing and sales practices.  Consumers of Yancey Events requested refunds ranging from $1,000 to more than $30,000, claiming the business did not deliver what it promised."'''</ref>

== Charity ==
In one episode of ''Flipping Vegas'', the Yanceys donated a home to a wounded veteran.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.reviewjournal.com/view/southwest/southwest-las-vegas-spotlight|title=Southwest Las Vegas in the spotlight|last=Mosier|first=Jeff|date=2012-04-17|work=Las Vegas Review-Journal|access-date=2016-07-13}}</ref>

== Publications ==
Yancey has published two books:
* ''Go Time'' (2012), a 250-page book inspired by people who taught Yancey about real estate.<ref>{{Cite book|url=https://www.amazon.com/Go-Time-Scott-Yancey/dp/B00BQLHR44|title=Go Time|last=Yancey|first=Scott|date=2012|publisher=Visionary Strategies|language=English}}</ref>
* ''Flipping Your Way to Real Estate Profits'' (2015), a 221-page book offering advice to financially challenged investors on how to make profits beyond flipping houses.<ref>{{Cite book|url=https://www.amazon.com/Flipping-Your-Real-Estate-Profits-ebook/dp/B00SG8FC38?ie=UTF8&ref_=asap_bc|title=Flipping Your Way to Real Estate Profits|last=Yancey|first=Scott|last2=Yancey|first2=Amie|date=2015-01-18|publisher=Yancey LLC|edition=1|language=English}}</ref>

